6
7 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk was a champion of free speech, civil
8 dialogue, and faith, and
9 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk consistently promoted the values of
10 individual liberty, open debate, civic engagement, and defense
11 of constitutional principles, and
12 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk believed in the power of free speech
13 and the open debate of ideas as the foundation of a free
14 society, and he dedicated his life to ensuring those principles
15 were upheld on college and university campuses and in public
16 life, and
17 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk was a co-founder and the executive
18 director of Turning Point USA, a nonprofit organization with
19 thousands of chapters nationwide, including active chapters at
20 colleges and universities across this state, where his work
21 inspired Florida students to embrace civic participation and the
22 principles of liberty and democracy, and
23 WHEREAS, through his public speaking, writing, and media
24 presence, Charlie Kirk reached millions of Americans, including
